# Hizal Development Rules

## What is Hizal?
Hizal is behavior-driven memory infrastructure for AI agents. Go API with PostgreSQL + pgvector for semantic search, MCP server over HTTP+SSE.

## Core Architecture

- **Three scopes:** PROJECT (shared), AGENT (private), ORG (org-wide)
- **always_inject:** Chunks surfaced automatically as ambient context
- **Purpose-built write tools:** write_identity, write_memory, write_knowledge, write_convention, write_org_knowledge, store_principle
- **Session lifecycle:** start_session → register_focus → work → end_session
- **No server-side LLM** — agents do all reasoning client-side

## Key Packages

- `internal/models` — canonical database-backed types (always scan rows here first)
- `internal/mcp/server.go` — MCP tool schemas and handlers
- `internal/api/` — HTTP handlers, middleware, CORS
- `internal/auth/` — API key generation, validation, scoping
- `internal/db/migrations/` — sequential migrations (up + down)
- `internal/embeddings/` — OpenAI text-embedding-3-small client

## API Key Format
```
ctx_{org-slug}_{random}
```
Never hardcode keys. Use `HIZAL_API_KEY` env var.

## MCP Tools (all in internal/mcp/server.go)

### Session
start_session, resume_session, get_active_session, register_focus, end_session

### Writes
write_identity (AGENT, always_inject), write_memory (AGENT), write_knowledge (PROJECT), write_convention (PROJECT, always_inject), write_org_knowledge (ORG), store_principle (ORG, always_inject, requires promoted_by_user_id)

### Reads
search_context, read_context, get_context_versions, compact_context

### Other
update_context, delete_context, review_context, write_context (deprecated)

### Admin
list_projects, list_agents, create_project, add_agent_to_project, remove_agent_from_project

## Coding Rules

- Standard Go (`gofmt`, `go vet`)
- All schema changes via `internal/db/migrations/`
- Every new table/column reflected in `internal/models`
- Error messages lowercase and descriptive
- Search before writing — no duplicate chunks
- Update `docs/03-mcp-tools.md` when changing tool schemas
- Update `internal/api/agent_onboarding_guide.go` if it affects onboarding
- Tests: `go test ./...`

## Chunk Types
KNOWLEDGE, MEMORY, CONVENTION, IDENTITY, PRINCIPLE, DECISION, RESEARCH, PLAN, SPEC, IMPLEMENTATION, CONSTRAINT, LESSON

## Agent Types (control tool visibility)
dev, admin, research, orchestrator
